The paired samples taken 2·3 and 6·0 years after vaccination showed the evolution of immunogenicity in the Ghanaian cohort. This group had a larger proportion of seropositive individuals 6·0 years after vaccination (43·1% [95% CI 38·5–47·8] 
 vs 27·8% [23·5–32·0]; 
 figure 1; 
 table 2). Year-6·0 antibody concentrations were also higher overall than the Ghana year-2·3 and the Mali year-4·5 values (
 figure 2B; 
 appendix p 4). 94 Ghanaian children were serostable over the intervening period, representing 77·7% of the year-2·3 positives and 21·6% of vaccinees (
 appendix pp 5–6).
